    "## 7. Business Cost Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "In fraud detection, the threshold choice is a **business decision**, not just an ML metric.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **False Negative** = missed fraud → bank absorbs the loss\n",
    "- **False Positive** = blocked legitimate transaction → customer frustration\n",
    "\n",
    "The right threshold depends on average fraud amount vs cost of customer churn."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "A lower threshold catches more fraud but inconveniences more customers.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "thresholds = np.percentile(r_ae['scores'], np.linspace(50, 99, 40))\n",
    "fn_list, fp_list = [], []\n",
    "for t in thresholds:\n",
    "    p  = (r_ae['scores'] >= t).astype(int)\n",
    "    cm = confusion_matrix(y, p)\n",
    "    fn_list.append(cm[1, 0])\n",
    "    fp_list.append(cm[0, 1])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
    "plt.plot(thresholds, fn_list, color='#D85A30', lw=2, label='Missed fraud (FN) — bank loss')\n",
    "plt.plot(thresholds, fp_list, color='#7F77DD', lw=2, label='Blocked legit (FP) — customer friction')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Threshold'); plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
    "plt.title('Business cost tradeoff — Autoencoder threshold')\n",
    "plt.legend(); plt.grid(alpha=0.3); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\n",
    "print('A lower threshold catches more fraud but inconveniences more customers.')"
   ]
